<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Online Compiler</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div id="header">
        <select id="languageDropdown">
            <option value="javascript">Nodejs</option>
            <option value="python">Python</option>
            <option value="java">Java</option>
        </select>
        <h1>Online Compiler</h1>
        <button id="runButton">Run</button>
    </div>

    <div id="editor-container">
        <div id="editor"></div>
        <div id="output-container">
            <div class="arg" style="display: flex;justify-content: space-between; padding-left: 20px;height: 50px;">
                <h2
                    style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 24px; color: #ff0000; text-align: center; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);">
                    Output</h2>
                <input type="text" id="argument1" placeholder="Enter your arguments here and please give a space">
            </div>
            <div id="output"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="editor-container1">
        <div id="project-notes">
            <h1>Note :</h1>
            <p>1)Please Note that if you code accepts some arguments from
                command line or using any inbuilt method like Scanner of java
                just add the arguments with a space between them in the input
                field above the output window.</p>
            <p>2)Please Note this compiler does not support gui based codes or framework
                this compiler is just for practice code or text based codes.</p>
            <p>3)You can install External Packages also just check on right side div.</p>
            <p>4)The code editor automatically gives you suggesstion like vscode does.</p>
            <p>5)We have used Monaco editor here which is same implemented on vscode. </p>
            <p>6)The Compiler only Supports nodejs or javascript ,python and java. </p>
        </div>
        <div id="installdependency">
            <div class="loading">
                <div class="anim"></div>
            </div>
            <h1>Install <br> External Packages</h1>
            <input type="text" id="packag" placeholder="Enter Package Name">
            <button onclick="startLoading()">Install</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="footer">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 3px;">Â© 2023 Coding.Alphas</h4>
        <h3> Developed By Nikhil</h3>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.socket.io/4.1.2/socket.io.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/monaco-editor@0.29.0/min/vs/loader.js"></script>
    <script src="script.js"></script>

</body>

</html>